claim.claim-text:
A charged particle beam system, comprising:
a source of charged particles forming a charged particle beam (106);
a focusing column (100) for focusing the charged particle beam onto a target (108);
a vacuum chamber containing a target stage for holding the target; and
an on-axis secondary particle detector (120) having an on-axis hole for passage of the primary beam and a detection portion;
characterized in that a field source (330a, 330b, 800, 900) is positioned between the target stage and the particle detector (320), the field source providing a field (303) to deflect secondary particles (316) away from the on-axis hole (313) in the secondary particle detector and onto the detection portion.

A method of detecting secondary particles, comprising:
directing a beam (106) of primary charged particles toward a target surface (108) in a target vacuum chamber;
collecting secondary charged particles emitted from the target surface upon impact of the beam of primary charged particles using a detector located above the target, the detector is configured with a center hole to permit the primary beam to pass through;
detecting the secondary particles (116) which have passed through the one or more of the grids in the multiplicity of grids;
characterized in
deflecting the secondary particles (316) away from center hole in the detector and toward a portion of the detector that detects the secondary particles.
